SIMPLE: rigorism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rigorism
<hw>Rig"or*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>rigorisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rigidity in principle or
practice; strictness; -- opposed to <ant>laxity</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Severity, as of style, or the like.</def>
<rj><au>Jefferson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Ethics)</fld> <def>Strictness in ethical
principles; -- usually applied to ascetic ethics, and opposed to ethical
<contr>latitudinarianism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigorist</ent>⟦br⟧
